    neo:id "ac606171fc7241d86df47e1bc2c03cea"^^xsd:string ;
    neo:source "/data/1957_-_Paul_Reps_-_Zen_flesh_zen_bones-A_Collection_of_Zen_and_Pre_Zen_Writings_-_Scan_by_OceanofPDF_dot_com_-_local_converter.md"^^xsd:string ;
    neo:text """I am existing. This is mine. This is this. 0 Beloved, even in such know illimitably. 107. This consciousness is the spirit of guidance of each one. Be this one.

Here is a sphere of change, change, change. Through change consume change.

As a hen mothers her chicks, mother particular knowings, particular doings, in reality.

Since, in truth, bondage and freedom are relative, these words are only for those terrified with the universe. This universe is a reflection of minds. As you see many suns in water from one sun, so see bondage and liberation.

Each thing is perceived through knowing. The self shines in space through knowing. Perceive one being as knower and known.

Beloved, at this moment let mind, knowing, breath, form, be included.

What Is Zen?

What Is Zen?

Try if you wish. But Zen comes of itself. True Zen shows in everyday living, CONSCIOUSNESS in action. More than any limited awareness, it opens every inner door to our infinite nature.

Instantly mind frees. How it frees! False Zen wracks brains as a fiction concocted by priests and salesmen to peddle their own wares.

Look at it this way, inside out and outside in: CONSCIOUSNESS everywhere, inclusive, through you. Then you can’t help living humbly, in wonder.

“What is Zen?”

One answer: Inayat Khan tells a Hindu story of a fish who went to a queen fish and asked: “I have always heard about the sea, but what is this sea? Where is it?”

The queen fish explained: “You live, move, and have your being in the sea. The sea is within you and without you, and you are made of sea, and you will end in sea. The sea surrounds you as your own being.”

Another answer: * “Mu” is the negative symbol in Chinese, meaning “No thing” or “Nay.”"""^^xsd:string .

ex:node_4_97c2bd02_e99e_4762_96d1_819e4ffdc573_477 a neo:Document ;
    neo:MENTIONS ex:node_4_97c2bd02_e99e_4762_96d1_819e4ffdc573_478 ;
    neo:id "9fb3069070530eb6d1c0de6a97347350"^^xsd:string ;
    neo:source "Source document: ZEN FLESH, ZEN BONES, Chapter: 8. Great Waves, paragraph number 4, sentence number 4 on page 21"^^xsd:string ;
    neo:text "You are those huge waves sweeping everything before them, swallowing all in their path."^^xsd:string .

ex:node_4_97c2bd02_e99e_4762_96d1_819e4ffdc573_479 a neo:Document ;
    neo:MENTIONS ex:node_4_97c2bd02_e99e_4762_96d1_819e4ffdc573_476,
